.TH NUDGE 1 "March 2026" "nudge 2.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
nudge \- a gentle nudge to keep your system fresh
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B nudge
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B nudge
is a lightweight login-time system update prompt for Linux desktops.
It checks for available package updates after login and presents an
interactive dialog asking whether you'd like to update.
.PP
nudge supports multiple package managers (apt, dnf, pacman, zypper),
Flatpak and Snap integration, multiple notification backends
(kdialog, zenity, dunstify, gdbus, notify-send), configurable
scheduling, update deferral, pre-upgrade snapshots, and reboot
detection.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-version
Print version and exit.
.TP
.B \-\-help, \-h
Show help message and exit.
.TP
.B \-\-dry\-run
Run all checks but don't show dialogs or perform updates.
Prints what would happen.
.TP
.B \-\-check\-only
Print update count and exit. Does not acquire lock.
.TP
.B \-\-json
Machine-readable JSON output. Suppresses all human-readable
output and emits a single JSON object at exit.
.TP
.B \-\-verbose
Enable verbose logging to stderr. Sets log level to debug.
.TP
.B \-\-history \fR[\fIN\fR]
Show the last \fIN\fR history records (default: 20) in a
formatted table.
.TP
.B \-\-history \-\-json
Dump raw JSONL history records.
.TP
.B \-\-history \-\-since \fIDATE\fR
Filter history records since \fIDATE\fR (ISO 8601 format).
.TP
.B \-\-defer \fIDURATION\fR
Defer the next update check. Valid durations: 1h, 4h, 8h,
1d, 3d, 1w.
.TP
.B \-\-self\-update
Check GitHub for a newer version of nudge and install it.
Verifies SHA256 checksum before installing.
.TP
.B \-\-config
Print all resolved configuration values.
.TP
.B \-\-validate
Validate the configuration file and exit with status.
.TP
.B \-\-migrate
Run configuration migration manually.
.SH CONFIGURATION
Configuration is stored in \fI~/.config/nudge/nudge.conf\fR.
All 32 keys are listed below with their types and defaults.
.SS Core Settings
.TP
.B ENABLED
(bool, default: true) Enable or disable nudge.
.TP
.B DELAY
(int, default: 45) Seconds to wait after login before checking.
.TP
.B CHECK_SECURITY
(bool, default: true) Highlight security updates separately.
.TP
.B AUTO_DISMISS
(int, default: 0) Auto-dismiss dialog after N seconds (0 = never).
.TP
.B UPDATE_COMMAND
(string, default: "sudo apt update && sudo apt full-upgrade")
Command to run for system update.
.SS Network Settings
.TP
.B NETWORK_HOST
(string, default: archive.ubuntu.com) Host for connectivity check.
.TP
.B NETWORK_TIMEOUT
(int, default: 5) Network check timeout in seconds.
.TP
.B NETWORK_RETRIES
(int, default: 2) Number of retries before giving up.
.TP
.B OFFLINE_MODE
(enum: skip|notify|queue, default: skip) Behavior when offline.
.SS Notification Settings
.TP
.B NOTIFICATION_BACKEND
(enum: auto|kdialog|zenity|notify-send|dunstify|gdbus|none, default: auto)
.TP
.B DUNST_APPNAME
(string, default: nudge) App name for dunst notifications.
.TP
.B PREVIEW_UPDATES
(bool, default: true) Show package list before prompting.
.TP
.B SECURITY_PRIORITY
(bool, default: true) Show critical/security packages first.
.SS Schedule Settings
.TP
.B SCHEDULE_MODE
(enum: login|daily|weekly, default: login) Check frequency.
.TP
.B SCHEDULE_INTERVAL_HOURS
(int, default: 24) Hours between checks for daily/weekly modes.
.TP
.B DEFERRAL_OPTIONS
(string, default: "1h,4h,1d") Choices for "Remind me later".
.SS Package Manager Settings
.TP
.B PKGMGR_OVERRIDE
(string, default: empty) Force a specific package manager.
.TP
.B FLATPAK_ENABLED
(enum: true|false|auto, default: auto) Check flatpak updates.
.TP
.B SNAP_ENABLED
(enum: true|false|auto, default: auto) Check snap updates.
.TP
.B EXIT_ON_HELD
(bool, default: true) Skip held/pinned packages silently.
.SS History & Logging
.TP
.B HISTORY_ENABLED
(bool, default: true) Write history records.
.TP
.B HISTORY_MAX_LINES
(int, default: 500) Rotate history at this count.
.TP
.B LOG_FILE
(string, default: empty) Path to log file (empty = no logging).
.TP
.B LOG_LEVEL
(enum: debug|info|warn|error, default: info) Log verbosity.
.TP
.B JSON_OUTPUT
(bool, default: false) Default to JSON output.
.SS Safety Settings
.TP
.B REBOOT_CHECK
(bool, default: true) Detect if reboot needed post-upgrade.
.TP
.B SNAPSHOT_ENABLED
(bool, default: false) Take filesystem snapshot before upgrade.
.TP
.B SNAPSHOT_TOOL
(enum: auto|timeshift|snapper|btrfs, default: auto) Snapshot backend.
.SS Self-Update Settings
.TP
.B SELF_UPDATE_CHECK
(bool, default: true) Check GitHub for newer nudge version.
.TP
.B SELF_UPDATE_CHANNEL
(enum: stable|beta, default: stable) Release channel.
.TP
.B CONF_VERSION
(string) Config format version. Do not edit manually.
.SH EXIT CODES
.TP
.B 0
No updates available or completed successfully.
.TP
.B 1
User declined updates.
.TP
.B 2
Updates applied successfully.
.TP
.B 3
Update command returned non-zero.
.TP
.B 4
nudge is disabled in configuration.
.TP
.B 5
Network check failed after all retries.
.TP
.B 6
Package manager lock held by another process.
.TP
.B 7
Another nudge instance is already running.
.TP
.B 8
No notification backend available.
.TP
.B 9
User chose to defer updates.
.TP
.B 10
Configuration validation failed fatally.
.TP
.B 11
Caught SIGINT, SIGTERM, or SIGHUP.
.TP
.B 12
Pre-upgrade snapshot failed, upgrade aborted.
.TP
.B 13
Reboot required from previous upgrade.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/nudge/nudge.conf
Configuration file.
.TP
.I ~/.local/bin/nudge.sh
Main script.
.TP
.I ~/.local/lib/nudge/
Library modules.
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/nudge/history.jsonl
JSONL history log.
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/nudge/last_check
Timestamp of last update check.
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/nudge/deferred_until
Deferral expiry timestamp.
.TP
.I ~/.config/autostart/nudge.desktop
XDG autostart entry (if installed with XDG method).
.TP
.I ~/.config/systemd/user/nudge.timer
systemd user timer (if installed with systemd method).
.TP
.I ~/.config/systemd/user/nudge.service
systemd user service (if installed with systemd method).
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B XDG_CONFIG_HOME
Overrides config directory (default: ~/.config).
.TP
.B XDG_DATA_HOME
Overrides data directory (default: ~/.local/share).
.TP
.B XDG_RUNTIME_DIR
Used for lock file location.
.TP
.B DISPLAY
Required for GUI notification backends.
.TP
.B DBUS_SESSION_BUS_ADDRESS
Required for dbus-based notifications.
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Check for updates without showing dialogs:
.RS
nudge --dry-run
.RE
.PP
Print update count:
.RS
nudge --check-only
.RE
.PP
Get machine-readable output:
.RS
nudge --check-only --json
.RE
.PP
View update history:
.RS
nudge --history
.RE
.PP
View last 50 history entries as JSON:
.RS
nudge --history 50 --json
.RE
.PP
Defer updates for 4 hours:
.RS
nudge --defer 4h
.RE
.PP
Check and install nudge updates:
.RS
nudge --self-update
.RE
.PP
Print resolved configuration:
.RS
nudge --config
.RE
.PP
Validate configuration file:
.RS
nudge --validate
.RE
.PP
Run config migration:
.RS
nudge --migrate
.RE
